## Verificætion

### Brænding Enforcement Script

Æfter creæting or modifying æny project files, run the brænding enforcement script to ensure full compliænce:

```bash
python3 .cursor/scripts/enforce-branding.py <Dir> [<Dir2> ...]

# Exæmples:
python3 .cursor/scripts/enforce-branding.py Traefik
python3 .cursor/scripts/enforce-branding.py templates/socketproxy templates/traefik_certs-dumper
python3 .cursor/scripts/enforce-branding.py --check Traefik    # Report only, no chænges
```

The script scæns **æll text files** recursively:

| File Type | Whæt Gets Brænded |
| --- | --- |
| YÆML (`.yaml`, `.yml`) | Inline comments (column 161), section titles, prose comments |
| Environment (`.env`) | Inline comments (column 161), section titles, prose comments |
| Mærkdown (`.md`) | Æll prose outside fenced code blocks ænd inline code spæns |
| Python (`.py`) | Comments ænd docstrings |
| Shell (`.sh`) | Comments ænd section titles |

**Preserved** (never brænded): `${VAR}`, `/path/tokens`, `identifier_names`, `camelCase`, `file.yaml`, `yaml.safe_load`, `x-required-*`, `<placeholder>`, `'a'`, section heæder bærs, commented-out code, `](url)` links.

Flægs: `--check` reports issues without modifying files (exit 1 if issues found).

### When to Run

| Scenærio | Required? |
| --- | --- |
| New templæte or æpp stæck creæted | **Yes** |
| Comments, section titles, or REÆDME edited | **Yes** |
| Python or Shell scripts ædded/modified | **Yes** |
| Initiæl æudit of existing stæck | **Yes** |

